<h1>Swift Toolchain Installation Guide for iOS 6</h1>

<h2>Step 1: Choose the Correct Swift Toolchain</h2>

<p><strong>Mojave:</strong> Use Swift 5.1.5</p>
<pre><code>// Official Swift 5.1.5
<a href="https://download.swift.org/swift-5.1.5-release/xcode/swift-5.1.5-RELEASE/swift-5.1.5-RELEASE-osx.pkg" target="_blank">Download Swift 5.1.5</a>

// Toolchain files & build script
<a href="https://github.com/JWIMaster/Swift-5.3.3-for-iOS-6/releases/tag/0.0.1" target="_blank">Download from GitHub</a>
</code></pre>

<p><strong>Big Sur or older:</strong> Use Swift 5.6 AND 5.1.5</p>
<pre><code>// Swift 5.6
<a href="https://download.swift.org/swift-5.6.3-release/xcode/swift-5.6.3-RELEASE/swift-5.6.3-RELEASE-osx.pkg" target="_blank">Download Swift 5.6.3</a>

// Swift 5.1.5
<a href="https://download.swift.org/swift-5.1.5-release/xcode/swift-5.1.5-RELEASE/swift-5.1.5-RELEASE-osx.pkg" target="_blank">Download Swift 5.1.5</a>

// Toolchain files & build script
<a href="https://github.com/JWIMaster/Swift-5.6.3-for-iOS-6/releases/tag/0.0.1" target="_blank">Download from GitHub</a>
</code></pre>

<p><strong>Monterey:</strong> Use Swift 5.10.1 AND 5.1.5</p>
<pre><code>// Swift 5.10.1
<a href="https://download.swift.org/swift-5.10.1-release/xcode/swift-5.10.1-RELEASE/swift-5.10.1-RELEASE-osx.pkg" target="_blank">Download Swift 5.10.1</a>

// Swift 5.1.5
<a href="https://download.swift.org/swift-5.1.5-release/xcode/swift-5.1.5-RELEASE/swift-5.1.5-RELEASE-osx.pkg" target="_blank">Download Swift 5.1.5</a>

// Toolchain files & build script
<a href="https://github.com/JWIMaster/Swift-5.10.1-for-iOS-6/releases/tag/0.0.1" target="_blank">Download from GitHub</a>
</code></pre>

<h2>Step 2: Install Xcode</h2>
<pre><code>// Recommended Xcode version by macOS
Mojave -> Xcode 11.3.1
Catalina -> Xcode 12.4
Big Sur -> Xcode 13.2
Monterey -> Xcode 13.4.1
</code></pre>

<h2>Step 3: Unzip Toolchain Files</h2>
<pre><code>// Open Finder
Control-Shift-G
Paste: /Library/Developer/Toolchains
</code></pre>

<p class="note">Important: Each toolchain folder (e.g., Swift-5.1.5-RELEASE) is the ROOT. Paths inside the zip are relative to this root.</p>

<h2>Step 4: Copy Files</h2>
<pre><code>// Example instruction from zip:
"Put into Swift 5.1.5 usr/lib/swift/iphoneos"

// Path in Finder:
/Library/Developer/Toolchains/swift-5.1.5-RELEASE.xctoolchain/usr/lib/swift/iphoneos

// Always select "Overwrite" when copying files
</code></pre>

<p class="note">Ensure you copy files into both 5.1.5 and the newer toolchain for macOS versions newer than Mojave. If not done correctly, reinstall the toolchains.</p>

<h2>Step 5: Done!</h2>
<p>Installation is complete. You can now move on to setting up your Swift project targeting iOS 6.</p>

